### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/Mpesa
@contentType = application/json

### 1. TEST PAYMENT INITIATION (STK PUSH)
# This simulates your React/Mobile App calling your backend
# Replace the phone with your own to get a real prompt on your phone!
POST {{baseUrl}}/stk-push
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "phoneNumber": "254112310754",
    "amount": 1,
    "bookingId": 101,
    "nationalId": 1234567823
}


### 2. TEST SUCCESS CALLBACK (MANUAL SIMULATION)
# Use this to test your Drizzle update logic without spending money.
# STEP 1: Run Request #1 above.
# STEP 2: Copy the "checkoutRequestId" from the response.
# STEP 3: Paste it into "CheckoutRequestID" below and send this request.
POST {{baseUrl}}/callback
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "Body": {
        "stkCallback": {
            "MerchantRequestID": "29115-3462721-1",
            "CheckoutRequestID": "ws_CO_02042026212109", 
            "ResultCode": 0,
            "ResultDesc": "The service request is processed successfully.",
            "CallbackMetadata": {
                "Item": [
                    { "Name": "Amount", "Value": 1.00 },
                    { "Name": "MpesaReceiptNumber", "Value": "RDK291J9S" },
                    { "Name": "TransactionDate", "Value": 20260402212109 },
                    { "Name": "PhoneNumber", "Value": 254712345678 }
                ]
            }
        }
    }
}


### 3. TEST FAILED CALLBACK (USER CANCELLED)
# Simulates a user hitting "Cancel" on the M-Pesa PIN prompt
POST {{baseUrl}}/callback
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "Body": {
        "stkCallback": {
            "MerchantRequestID": "29115-3462721-1",
            "CheckoutRequestID": "ws_CO_02042026212109",
            "ResultCode": 1032,
            "ResultDesc": "Request cancelled by user."
        }
    }
}